            . I live with my father and mother, in St. Andrew-street, Seven Dials, and sell onions in the street. On the 13th of December, a little after seven o'clock, I was near Stephens' shop, in <placeName id="t18280110-160-crimeloc839">Church-passage, St. Giles'</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-160-crimeloc839" type="placeName" value="Church-passage, St. Giles'"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-160-crimeloc839" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-160-off837 t18280110-160-crimeloc839"></join>. I knew the prisoner before; Oldfield lives in Crown-street. I saw Oldfield run towards me, with the clothes in his hand - Geddes was with him; the jacket and trousers were buttoned together; they were only a few yards from the shop; Oldfield gave them to Geddes, and when they had ran further, Oldfield took them again, and put them under his coat; they offered them to me, but I would not take them; they ran down Monmouth-street, into a coach-yard; the officer came and took us all three.</p>
               <p>Prisoner GEDDES. Q. Did you not stand at the end of the street, on purpose to take them? A. No.</p>
